com.camerontec.util.datamodel.message

Class AnyFieldValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.message.AnyFieldValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Encodable, FieldValue, Recyclable

    public final class AnyFieldValue
extends Object
implements FieldValue
    Field implementation capable of containing a value of any of the supported types.

    At any time a field has a specific value and type. The is determined as follows:

    • Whenever a new value is set explicitly via any of the setType() family of methods the field inherits the type of the supplied value
    • The type is not modified by any of the asType() family of methods unless the type is currently a byte vector, in which case the field inherits the requested type and the decoder is used to obtain the value

    Some, but not all, type conversions are supported. In particular:

    • Conversion from byte array to any type is support via decoding - see Decoder
    • Conversion from any type to String is supported
    • Conversions between numeric types are supported provided the result is in range for the requested type
    • Conversion to double is similarly supported, however, in the case of an out of range value (e.g. a very large or small positive or negative java.math.BigInteger or java.math.BigDecimal) an FieldException is thrown rather than forcing the caller to check for Double.isInfinite() or Double.isNaN()

    This class is not thread safe.
